11 An Act relating to social media; providing
legislative intent; defining terms; prohibiting
12 minors under sixteen years of age from being an
account holder on certain social media platforms;
13 prohibiting minors older than sixteen years of age
from being an account holder on certain social media
14 platforms without express consent of parent or legal
guardian; requiring verification of account holder's
15 age; permitting the use of third-party vendors to
verify age; prohibiting social media platforms
16 accessed by minors from engaging in certain
activities; stating that violations may be reported
17 to the Office of the Attorney General; permitting the
Office of the Attorney General to send notice;
18 clarifying social media platforms shall have a period
to cure violations; clarifying when a social media
19 company is liable for failure to comply; permitting
the Attorney General to initiate an enforcement
20 action; providing exemptions; limiting liability;
prohibiting commercial entities or third-party
21 vendors from retaining certain information;
establishing liability for failure to comply;
22 providing for noncodification; providing for
codification; providing an effective date; and
23 declaring an emergency.
