1 A. A social media company shall not permit an Oklahoma user who
2 is a minor less than sixteen (16) years of age to be an account
3 holder on a social media company's social media platform.
4 B. A social media company shall not permit an Oklahoma user who
5 is a minor of sixteen (16) or seventeen (17) years of age to be an
6 account holder on the social media company's social media platform
7 unless the minor has the express consent of a parent or legal
8 guardian.
9 C. 1. A social media company shall verify the age of an
10 account holder.
11 2. If an account holder is a minor of sixteen (16) or seventeen
12 (17) years of age, the social media company shall confirm that the
13 minor has consent under subsection B of this section to become a new
14 account holder at the time the Oklahoma user opens the account.
15 D. 1. A social media company may use a third-party vendor to
16 perform reasonable age verification before allowing access to the
17 social media company's social media platform.
18 2. Reasonable age verification methods under paragraph 1 of
19 this subsection include providing:
20 a. a digitized identification card, including a digital
21 copy of a driver license,
22 b. government-issued identification,
23 c. any commercially reasonable age verification method,
24 or
